## CheckCaptcha API
To verify the answers of the made captcha E0(response token) and to identify the procedures of the response `n=` which is the hcaptcha fingerprint. Which then tells the checkcaptcha api to throw back a P0(final token).

| URL | Method |
| - | - |
| https://hcaptcha.com/checkcaptcha/${key} | `POST` |

In response you will get the `generated_pass_UUID` solved token.

# Query Parameters
- `answers`: solved task key usually looks like this: 37826178-9fa4-4388-ab2f-d9d3520a334e : true / false
- `sitekey`: hcaptcha sitekey
- `server_domain`: www.google.com or whatever is connected to the API
- `job_mode`: image_label_binary
- `motion_data`: includes mouse_movement / keyboard input etc...
- `n`: the hsl which is encoded in base64
- `c`: the old req value from the checksiteconfig request

    "expiration": 120
}
